          30-3-35.1(5)(e): ability to provide appropriate playtime with the child;
          30-3-35.1(5)(f): history and ability of the noncustodial parent to implement a flexible schedule for the child;
          30-3-35.1(5)(g): physical facilities of the noncustodial parent's residence; and
          30-3-35.1(5)(h): any other factor the court considers relevant.
      30-3-35.1(6): If the parties agree or the court enters an order for the optional parent-time schedule under this section, a parenting plan in compliance with Sections 30-3-10.7[Ref: 30-3-10.7] 30-3-10.10[Ref: 30-3-10.10] Subsection 7[Ref: 30-3-35.1(7)]
