                  30-3-35.1(7)(a)(ii)(B): if there is no school, the noncustodial parent is available to be with the child, and in accommodation with the custodial parent's work schedule, beginning at 8 a.m. and ending on the following day upon delivering the child to school or at 8 a.m. if there is no school;
          30-3-35.1(7)(b): 
              30-3-35.1(7)(b)(i): beginning the first weekend after the entry of the decree, alternating weekends beginning at 6 p.m. on Friday and ending on Monday upon delivering the child to school or at 8 a.m. if there is no school; or
              30-3-35.1(7)(b)(ii): at the election of the noncustodial parent, beginning the first weekend after the entry of the decree, alternating weekends:
                  30-3-35.1(7)(b)(ii)(A): beginning at the time the child's school is regularly dismissed on Friday and ending on Monday upon delivering the child to school or at 8 a.m. if there is no school; or
                  30-3-35.1(7)(b)(ii)(B): if there is no school, the noncustodial parent is available to be with the child, and in accommodation with the custodial parent's work schedule, beginning on Friday at 9 a.m. and ending on Monday upon delivering the child to school or at 8 a.m. if there is no school;
          30-3-35.1(7)(c): each holiday granted to the noncustodial parent in accordance with the holiday schedule described in Subsection 16[Ref: 30-3-35.1(16)]
          30-3-35.1(7)(d): extended parent-time with the child when school is not in session for summer break in accordance with Subsection 8[Ref: 30-3-35.1(8)]
      30-3-35.1(8): 
          30-3-35.1(8)(a): For extended parent-time with the child under Subsection d[Ref: 30-3-35.1(7)(d)]
          30-3-35.1(8)(b): For the four weeks of extended parent-time for a noncustodial parent under Subsection a[Ref: 30-3-35.1(8)(a)]
              30-3-35.1(8)(b)(i): two weeks, which may be consecutive, shall be uninterrupted parent-time for the noncustodial parent; and
              30-3-35.1(8)(b)(ii): two weeks, which may be consecutive, may be interrupted by the custodial parent for a weekday visit on the same day on which the noncustodial parent is granted weekday day parent-time.
          30-3-35.1(8)(c): A custodial parent is entitled to uninterrupted parent-time with the child for two weeks, which may be consecutive, when school is not in session for summer break.
      30-3-35.1(9): 
          30-3-35.1(9)(a): Each parent shall provide notification to the other parent of the parent's plans for the exercise of parent-time for summer break under Subsection 8[Ref: 30-3-35.1(8)]
          30-3-35.1(9)(b): For the notification requirement under Subsection a[Ref: 30-3-35.1(9)(a)]
              30-3-35.1(9)(b)(i): in odd-numbered years:
